    </section>

    <section id="executive-summary" class="section">
      <h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>
      <p>This report documents a comprehensive image analysis exercise conducted during this chat session. Two distinct image sets were examined:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>RAG Database Images</strong> — six fantasy-themed icon graphics stored in the Image Sets RAG library</li>
        <li><strong>_IMG3766.JPG</strong> — a user-uploaded beach photograph</li>
      </ol>
      <p>The analysis compared vision-model-generated descriptions against direct pixel-level inspection. Both image sets achieved approximately <strong>85–90% accuracy</strong>. In both cases, the most consistent issue was <strong>over-specification</strong>: the model often stated details with more confidence than the raw image evidence fully supported.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="image-sets" class="section">
      <h2>2. Image Sets Analyzed</h2>
      <div class="grid-2">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>2.1 RAG Database Images (Fantasy Icon Set)</h3>
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Image ID</th><th>Filename</th><th>Description Summary</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
